Method Detail

getLabelEditorComponent

ItsNatComponent getLabelEditorComponent(ItsNatLabel label,
                                        java.lang.Object value,
                                        org.w3c.dom.Element labelElem)
Returns the component used to edit in place the label value.

Default implementation uses a ItsNatHTMLInputText (text not formatted version) to edit the label value.

Parameters:
label - the label component, may be used to provide contextual information. Default implementation ignores it.
value - the value to edit (initial value).
labelElem - the label element to render the value into. Is a hint, if provided should be obtained by calling ItsNatElementComponent.getElement().
Returns:
the component used to edit in place the label value. Current implementation of labels does nothing with this component and may be null (is not mandatory to use a single component as an editor).
See Also:
ItsNatLabel.setItsNatLabelEditor(ItsNatLabelEditor)
